Premium File Shares provide high-performance file storage backed by SSDs, suitable for enterprise workloads that require low latency and high IOPS.

They support SMB and NFS protocols and are ideal for applications requiring shared file access.

For example, enterprise applications like SAP or databases can use premium file shares for high-speed file operations.

A real-life use case is migrating on-premise file servers with performance-critical workloads to Azure.

Another example is hosting shared configurations or application data for multiple VMs.

Premium file shares ensure reliability and fast access for demanding workloads.
